Oh yeah. Well, the framebuffer area still hasn't changed though. You can DMA 14,233 bytes in a frame, and the frame buffer is 31,104 bytes, so you can almost have the game run at 30fps. I personally would settle for a lower frame rate and resolution for having about 16x the amount of color.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6683">Espozo</a> — Sat Feb 07, 2015 10:51 pm</p><hr />
