<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12351&amp;p=140775#p140775"><![CDATA[
DMA on Super NES is controlled by the CPU. It runs at 2.7 MHz, the speed of slow ROM and WRAM. This is the same as half the dot rate, as a dot is 4 master clocks, and a slow ROM cycle is 8 master clocks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Feb 07, 2015 6:45 pm</p><hr />
